WEBVTT

00:01.135 --> 00:03.537
Frank: Pecos, Texas,
back in the '70s --

00:03.571 --> 00:05.273
Me and the fellas
would meet up after school

00:05.306 --> 00:07.108
and play cops and robbers.

00:07.141 --> 00:08.709
They would all fight
to play the police officers.

00:08.742 --> 00:11.145
No one wanted to be a criminal
except me.

00:11.179 --> 00:13.247
I loved it,
because in my family,

00:13.281 --> 00:15.249
being a crook
was a point of pride.

00:15.283 --> 00:16.717
As far
as my daddy was concerned,

00:16.750 --> 00:19.120
breaking the law
was a badge of honor.

00:19.153 --> 00:22.156
[ Dramatic music plays ]

00:25.593 --> 00:27.561
[ Guns cock ]

00:27.828 --> 00:31.132
[ Exhales sharply ]
Sure you up for this, son?

00:31.165 --> 00:32.566
Daddy, I'm good to go.

00:35.169 --> 00:38.706
Am I really the one you should
be concerned about right now?

00:38.739 --> 00:40.308
Sliger, you all right?

00:40.341 --> 00:42.843
This is the best part --
watching them.

00:42.876 --> 00:44.578
[ Chuckles ]

00:45.346 --> 00:47.148
Where'd you find
this psycho?

00:47.181 --> 00:48.182
[ Shotgun cocks ]

00:51.619 --> 00:53.454
Man: Yes, this is
the one I spoke of.

00:53.487 --> 00:55.189
You can see right here...

00:55.223 --> 00:57.558
[ Doorbell chimes ]
On your knees, pee-paw!

00:57.591 --> 00:59.160
Away from the alarms,
everybody!

00:59.193 --> 01:00.494
Keep your hands
nice and high!

01:00.528 --> 01:01.729
That's it!

01:06.334 --> 01:07.568
Hurry, son!
Let's go! Let's go!

01:07.601 --> 01:09.203
I'm on it, Pop.

01:09.237 --> 01:10.204
Easy.

01:12.740 --> 01:14.875
Sliger: Oh.

01:14.908 --> 01:17.478
Ohh, what do we have here?

01:17.511 --> 01:20.080
[ Keypad beeps ]
It's armed.
Let's go.

01:23.484 --> 01:24.452
[ Whimpering ]

01:24.485 --> 01:27.488
Shh.
There, there, don't cry.

01:28.489 --> 01:30.191
Leave her alone.
Take -- Aah!

01:30.224 --> 01:31.225
Aah!

01:33.494 --> 01:36.664
It's okay. It's okay.
It's okay.

01:38.266 --> 01:41.202
-Cash.
-Look at all this.

01:41.235 --> 01:44.205
Don't be scared.
Don't be scared.
[ Crying ]

01:44.238 --> 01:45.339
[ Laughs ]

01:45.373 --> 01:46.340
[ Sobbing ]
It's okay.

01:46.374 --> 01:48.376
[ Pistol cocks ]
Drop it!

01:48.409 --> 01:49.377
[ Grunts ]

01:51.712 --> 01:53.214
I should've
let him kill you!

01:53.247 --> 01:54.282
Come on!
We got to move!

01:54.315 --> 01:55.683
Go! Go!

01:57.951 --> 02:01.121
[ Rock music plays ]

02:11.599 --> 02:13.767
Hey, Kyle.

02:13.801 --> 02:15.135
Come on in.

02:19.540 --> 02:21.442
You and Frank
live together?

02:21.475 --> 02:22.510
Me live here?

02:22.543 --> 02:23.944
[ Laughs ]
Please.

02:23.977 --> 02:25.446
Okay, 'cause I was
about to say

02:25.479 --> 02:27.315
this is so not you...

02:27.348 --> 02:29.650
yet so very Frank.
[ Lock clicks ]

02:29.683 --> 02:32.386
Oh, well, we're having
a little slumber party

02:32.420 --> 02:35.389
while the floors in my condo
are being refinished.

02:35.423 --> 02:38.659
Speaking of, it's sweet of you
to give up your day off

02:38.692 --> 02:40.594
to help Frank
with his home repairs.

02:40.628 --> 02:41.929
Home repairs?

02:41.962 --> 02:43.797
Frank sent a text saying
our day off was canceled

02:43.831 --> 02:45.666
because we had to work
on a case.

02:45.699 --> 02:46.967
That's right, trainee.

02:47.000 --> 02:48.602
We have to work
on a case of cervezas

02:48.636 --> 02:51.472
while fixing the hole
en el techo de mi casa.

02:51.505 --> 02:52.940
What the hell happened?

02:52.973 --> 02:54.408
[ Chuckling ] Oh, well...
[ Laughs ]

02:54.442 --> 02:55.843
it's -- it's kind of
a funny story.

02:57.478 --> 02:59.780
About four months ago,
this house was a heroin factory.

03:01.315 --> 03:02.950
Afternoon, ladies.
-Let's see your hands!

03:02.983 --> 03:05.686
Frank: We were here
serving a trafficking warrant

03:05.719 --> 03:07.288
when the deed holder...
[ Shotgun cocks ]

03:07.321 --> 03:08.622
tried to give me both barrels
of her sawed-off.

03:08.656 --> 03:10.891
I knocked the said sawed-off
up in the air,

03:10.924 --> 03:13.694
and that crazy gal turned
her ceiling into a sunroof.

03:13.727 --> 03:15.729
You literally
moved into a crime scene?

03:15.763 --> 03:18.432
To get this view of downtown,
hell yes, I did.

03:18.466 --> 03:19.767
Right after the bust,
I bribed a guy

03:19.800 --> 03:21.435
down at the seized-property
police auction

03:21.469 --> 03:24.305
and got this place
for a crackhead discount.

03:24.338 --> 03:25.439
[ Cellphone rings ]

03:25.473 --> 03:27.641
It's Detective Val Chavez.

03:27.675 --> 03:29.610
Hit "ignore" for me, babe.
Val knows it's my day off.
[ Cellphone beeps ]

03:29.643 --> 03:30.978
Yeah, mine, too.

03:31.011 --> 03:32.580
Goodbye, Frank.
I'm not your damn handyman.

03:32.613 --> 03:33.881
Wait, hold on now.

03:33.914 --> 03:34.848
[ Cellphone rings ]
Val.

03:34.882 --> 03:36.717
Again, "ignore."

03:36.750 --> 03:38.319
[ Cellphone beeps ]
You're looking at this
all wrong, Kyle.

03:38.352 --> 03:40.721
No, you're not my handyman,
but you are my trainee.

03:40.754 --> 03:43.491
So think of me as Mr. Miyagi,
and you're Daniel-san.

03:43.524 --> 03:47.027
I'm gonna show you
how to wax on, wax off my roof

03:47.060 --> 03:48.462
so you can get
your skills up

03:48.496 --> 03:49.663
and kick ass
in the big karate tournament

03:49.697 --> 03:50.731
at the end of the movie.

03:50.764 --> 03:52.333
See?
This is for your benefit.

03:52.366 --> 03:54.001
[ Cellphone rings ]

03:54.034 --> 03:56.470
If that's Val,
don't answer it.
[ Cellphone beeps ]

03:56.504 --> 03:58.339
Hey, Val.

03:58.372 --> 04:00.374
Why, yes,
he's right here.

04:00.408 --> 04:01.775
[ Sighs ]

04:03.811 --> 04:05.479
[ Siren wails ]
Thank you, Mr. Reo.

04:05.513 --> 04:08.015
If you could just wait
over there.

04:08.048 --> 04:09.883
[ Police radio chatter,
camera shutter clicking ]

04:09.917 --> 04:11.752
Hey, Frank.
-Don't, "Hey, Frank," me.

04:11.785 --> 04:12.920
I know I'm a dinosaur,

04:12.953 --> 04:14.555
but we got to bridge
this generation gap.

04:14.588 --> 04:17.491
Rule one -- Unless it's
an absolute emergency,

04:17.525 --> 04:20.761
never ever call me in
on the most sacred of holy days,

04:20.794 --> 04:22.630
my God-given day off.

04:22.663 --> 04:25.366
Amen.
Hey, don't get your chonies
in a bunch, Francesca.

04:25.399 --> 04:27.501
It wasn't my call.

04:27.535 --> 04:29.036
You see that guy there?

04:29.069 --> 04:30.904
Name's Mike Reo.

04:30.938 --> 04:32.840
He's the proprietor
of this shop,

04:32.873 --> 04:34.975
and when he's not peddling
overpriced rocks,

04:35.008 --> 04:38.045
he's playing golf
with his local city councilman.

04:38.078 --> 04:41.048
That's who wants you working
on your day off, not me.

04:41.081 --> 04:43.050
Fine.
Take us through the robbery.

04:43.083 --> 04:44.952
Three suspects --

04:44.985 --> 04:46.387
Two blow the safe
in the back

04:46.420 --> 04:48.055
while the third covers
the front.

04:48.088 --> 04:50.924
Gets a little handsy with
that clerk over there, Michelle.

04:50.958 --> 04:53.561
But the idiot pulls off
his glove to do it

04:53.594 --> 04:55.929
and reveals a tattoo
on his left hand --

04:55.963 --> 04:57.665
black widow spider.

04:57.698 --> 04:58.932
I'll run it
through the database.

04:58.966 --> 05:00.534
Maybe we'll get lucky.

05:00.568 --> 05:01.969
So, the guard decides
to go for his backup.

05:02.002 --> 05:03.404
Suspect two comes out.

05:03.437 --> 05:05.606
Bang --
The guard dies instantly.

05:05.639 --> 05:07.007
Frank: [ Sighs ]

05:12.446 --> 05:14.748
This has a Southeast stamp
on it.

05:14.782 --> 05:16.750
Guard was a cop?

05:16.784 --> 05:19.587
Gus Ochoa --
30 years on the job.

05:19.620 --> 05:20.954
Spoke with his wife.

05:20.988 --> 05:23.457
Said he went stir crazy
in retirement.

05:23.491 --> 05:25.959
He only took the guard job
so he could protect and serve.

05:25.993 --> 05:27.961
Didn't even need the money.

05:27.995 --> 05:29.730
Kyle: Survived three decades
working in Watts

05:29.763 --> 05:32.433
only to be gunned down
in a Westwood jewelry store.

05:32.466 --> 05:33.501
What a waste.

05:33.534 --> 05:35.102
"Waste"?

05:35.135 --> 05:37.971
He was a south-end gunfighter
who died in a gunfight.

05:38.005 --> 05:39.473
Hell, I'll take
a blaze of glory

05:39.507 --> 05:41.709
over bed sores
in a nursing home any day.

05:41.742 --> 05:44.612
I'd say Gus went out
the way he wanted to.

05:48.816 --> 05:51.852
[ Train whistle blows
in distance ]

05:51.885 --> 05:54.388
* On a warm summer's eve

05:54.422 --> 05:57.057
* On a train bound for nowhere

05:57.090 --> 05:59.727
* I met up with a gambler

05:59.760 --> 06:02.463
* We were both too tired to
sleep *

06:02.496 --> 06:04.598
* So we took turns a-starin'
Sam: Frank.

06:04.632 --> 06:07.768
* Out the window
at the darkness *
Your daddy home?

06:07.801 --> 06:10.137
Daddy.

06:10.170 --> 06:12.506
Ranger's asking for you.

06:18.078 --> 06:20.514
Afternoon, Sam.

06:20.548 --> 06:22.750
You thirsty?
No, no.

06:22.783 --> 06:24.785
I'm on duty, Emmet.

06:24.818 --> 06:26.153
Home repairs, huh?

06:26.186 --> 06:28.889
Yeah.
Roof sprung a leak.

06:28.922 --> 06:30.524
Truth is, I don't mind
a few raindrops

06:30.558 --> 06:31.759
falling on my head,

06:31.792 --> 06:34.728
but a child needs
proper covering.

06:35.829 --> 06:37.898
You hear about this rash
of armed robberies...

06:37.931 --> 06:39.900
going around downtown?
-Whew!

06:39.933 --> 06:43.504
You talking
about the stickup man

06:43.537 --> 06:45.172
Pecos Police
can't seem to catch?

06:45.205 --> 06:47.174
Sam: Yeah, well,
they don't have to.

06:47.207 --> 06:49.777
The Texas Rangers
are on the case now.

06:49.810 --> 06:51.812
Just a matter of time
before that jackeroo

06:51.845 --> 06:54.181
wins free room and board
at the Huntsville Penitentiary.

06:54.214 --> 06:57.918
I'm a two-time graduate of that
fine correctional institution.

06:57.951 --> 07:01.789
One more stay,
and I'll earn my PhD.

07:01.822 --> 07:03.056
Well, here's the deal --

07:03.090 --> 07:06.527
So far, no one's been hurt --
praise God --

07:06.560 --> 07:09.830
so if this stickup man
retires,

07:09.863 --> 07:11.799
I mean for good,

07:11.832 --> 07:14.802
I'd be willing
to let bygones be bygones

07:14.835 --> 07:16.203
for old time's sake.

07:16.236 --> 07:18.105
You ain't gone soft
on me, Sam.

07:18.138 --> 07:19.807
Well, maybe
I'm being amenable

07:19.840 --> 07:22.476
because this bandit
might be a widower

07:22.510 --> 07:24.878
trying to raise
a young boy.

07:24.912 --> 07:27.114
A fine young man
needs proper covering.

07:28.716 --> 07:31.218
You know, Emmet, they say that
pride is the sin of all sins,

07:31.251 --> 07:33.587
and I must confess
to a certain pride

07:33.621 --> 07:34.822
bringing bad men to justice,

07:34.855 --> 07:36.724
but, uh,
there'd be no joy

07:36.757 --> 07:41.094
in shipping a good boy
off to foster care.

07:41.128 --> 07:42.863
Not if there's
another way.

07:45.599 --> 07:47.768
You know what, Sam?

07:47.801 --> 07:49.136
I got a feeling
you ain't gonna have

07:49.169 --> 07:51.471
any more troubles
from that bandit.

07:53.006 --> 07:55.108
I sure hope so.

07:55.142 --> 07:57.978
Well, best of luck
mending your roof.

07:58.011 --> 07:59.112
Mm.

07:59.146 --> 08:02.149
[ Dog barks in distance ]

08:09.890 --> 08:11.825
[ Engine starts ]

08:21.669 --> 08:24.004
You really gonna stop
pulling robberies?

08:24.037 --> 08:25.873
[ Chuckles ]

08:25.906 --> 08:28.041
[ Laughs ]

08:29.109 --> 08:31.612
Daddy,
if you go back to Huntsville,

08:31.645 --> 08:32.880
what happens to me?

08:32.913 --> 08:35.015
Ain't nobody gonna put me
back in a cage.

08:35.048 --> 08:37.885
So if that self-righteous
son of a bitch

08:37.918 --> 08:41.188
ever tries to take me down,
well, Frank,

08:41.221 --> 08:43.056
I'll send him home

08:43.090 --> 08:45.225
to that savior
he's so fond of.

08:47.327 --> 08:48.896
Kyle:
[ Echoing ] Frank?

08:48.929 --> 08:50.698
Frank.
-Hey. Still with us?

08:50.731 --> 08:53.066
-What?
-Everything all right?

08:54.201 --> 08:56.203
A member of the family
is dead on the floor,

08:56.236 --> 08:58.071
so you tell me
if everything's all right.

09:00.340 --> 09:03.644
Hope you brought
your ass-kicking shoes, trainee.

09:03.677 --> 09:04.745
You're gonna need them.

09:05.846 --> 09:07.815
**

09:07.848 --> 09:09.717
[ Siren wails,
police radio chatter ]

09:23.831 --> 09:25.232
What do you got, ladies?

09:25.265 --> 09:26.800
There's only one lady here,

09:26.834 --> 09:28.268
and she's got pretty blue eyes
and a beard.

09:28.301 --> 09:30.604
Oh, so you like
my baby blues?

09:30.638 --> 09:31.972
Frank: I'm pressing
the "pause" button

09:32.005 --> 09:33.373
on this little after-school
special of yours.

09:33.406 --> 09:34.808
We got a retired cop
in the morgue.

09:34.842 --> 09:36.209
Now, where are we?

09:36.243 --> 09:38.712
We I.D.'d the suspects using
their silicone-mask M.O.

09:38.746 --> 09:40.881
Matched it to a series
of hold-ups across the U.S.

09:40.914 --> 09:42.750
Came back to two cowboys
out of Oklahoma,

09:42.783 --> 09:44.952
Henry Hollister
and his 17-year-old son, Bobby.

09:44.985 --> 09:47.888
Only no one's been able to make
a case stick against these guys.

09:47.921 --> 09:49.823
They're smart --
never leave evidence,

09:49.857 --> 09:51.258
never stay in the same town
more than a week.

09:51.291 --> 09:53.160
And they're unplugged
completely --

09:53.193 --> 09:54.394
no cellphones,
no e-mails,

09:54.427 --> 09:56.129
no credit cards,
no bank account.

09:56.163 --> 09:58.932
Like they stepped
out of a time machine.

10:00.267 --> 10:01.769
So, who's the third guy?

10:01.802 --> 10:03.704
No idea.
Feels local, though.

10:03.737 --> 10:05.372
This was
their first major heist.

10:05.405 --> 10:06.907
Looks like up to now

10:06.940 --> 10:08.709
it's just been liquor stores
and supermarkets.

10:08.742 --> 10:10.310
My guess is
Henry brought in local talent

10:10.343 --> 10:11.912
to act as training wheels
for his son.

10:11.945 --> 10:13.213
Bet he's
regretting that now.

10:14.414 --> 10:16.016
See there?

10:16.049 --> 10:19.019
Henry wouldn't let his son
take the kill shot.

10:19.052 --> 10:20.320
Henry's paternal instincts
kicked in.

10:20.353 --> 10:22.022
He's protecting his boy.

10:22.055 --> 10:25.392
Henry knows
taking a life changes you.

10:25.425 --> 10:27.895
No man wants that
for his son.

10:31.298 --> 10:33.000
Henry: Hmm.
[ Whistles ]

10:33.033 --> 10:35.736
Rule number one -- Come out
richer than you were going in.

10:35.769 --> 10:37.304
[ Door opens, closes ]

10:38.171 --> 10:41.675
Rule number two --
Don't forget rule number one.

10:41.709 --> 10:43.343
[ Chuckles ]

10:43.376 --> 10:45.813
[ Train whistle blows
in distance ]

10:45.846 --> 10:48.048
What? You still pissed
about offing the old man?

10:48.081 --> 10:50.283
He went for his burner.
You had to put him down.

10:50.317 --> 10:52.920
Only because you weren't
about your business in there.

10:52.953 --> 10:56.156
But guess what, Sliger --
You're out.

10:56.189 --> 11:00.227
Divvy up the loot here
and part company.

11:00.260 --> 11:02.329
Fine. Fine.

11:02.362 --> 11:04.331
But then again...
[ Pistols cock ]

11:04.364 --> 11:07.100
jewels always split better
one way than they do three.

11:07.134 --> 11:08.902
Mister, take that gun
off my daddy.

11:08.936 --> 11:12.039
Bobby, do not pull
that trigger.
Listen to him, kid.

11:12.072 --> 11:13.340
Come on, even if you score
a head shot,

11:13.373 --> 11:14.975
there's probably still
enough juice left in here

11:15.008 --> 11:17.444
to send one last message
to my finger.

11:17.477 --> 11:18.779
Boom.

11:18.812 --> 11:21.181
Sliger, do me a favor.

11:21.214 --> 11:22.449
[ Jewels jingle ]

11:22.482 --> 11:25.052
Tonight, have yourself
a real fine time.

11:25.085 --> 11:27.054
I mean it, man.

11:27.087 --> 11:28.989
Go full Charlie Sheen.

11:29.022 --> 11:30.824
'Cause tomorrow morning...

11:32.392 --> 11:34.094
you're dead.

11:39.967 --> 11:41.969
[ Laughs ]

11:47.975 --> 11:50.310
Well, we're nice
and screwed now, Pop.

11:52.512 --> 11:54.181
This is all we got.

12:04.557 --> 12:06.493
He's re-watched that
like a dozen times.

12:06.526 --> 12:08.862
What's wrong with him?
-Not a damn thing.

12:08.896 --> 12:11.064
He's scouting out
the other team.
Just getting
in their heads.

12:14.534 --> 12:15.903
But seriously,

12:15.936 --> 12:17.104
what the hell's wrong
with Frank?

12:17.137 --> 12:19.406
-Find something?
-Bobby's a good kid.

12:19.439 --> 12:22.509
Not the ice-cold operator
his dad is.

12:22.542 --> 12:25.012
Look how he reacts
when his father kills the guard.

12:25.045 --> 12:27.014
[ Keyboard clicks ]

12:27.047 --> 12:28.415
Yeah.

12:28.448 --> 12:30.417
That kid
still has a chance.

12:30.450 --> 12:32.185
How could you possibly
know that?

12:33.186 --> 12:34.421
Aren't you supposed
to be trying to identify

12:34.454 --> 12:35.989
the suspect
with the black widow tattoo?

12:36.023 --> 12:37.390
I already did.

12:37.424 --> 12:38.926
How'd you do it that fast?

12:38.959 --> 12:41.128
Haven't you figured it out yet?
I'm good.

12:41.161 --> 12:42.529
[ Keyboard clacks ]

12:42.562 --> 12:44.998
Pored through photos
of tattoos from parolees.

12:45.032 --> 12:46.399
Found several
with black widow tats

12:46.433 --> 12:48.902
on left hands, but only one
with a rap sheet

12:48.936 --> 12:50.904
filled with high-end,
armed robberies.

12:50.938 --> 12:53.206
[ Keyboard clacks ]
Name's Leon Sliger.

12:53.240 --> 12:55.008
Just got off
with his parole officer.

12:55.042 --> 12:57.144
She says he hasn't
checked in for weeks,

12:57.177 --> 12:59.479
and his current address
and cellphone are bogus.

12:59.512 --> 13:01.348
Did the parole officer give you
anything we can check him with?

13:01.381 --> 13:03.316
Only that Sliger
never uses his real name,

13:03.350 --> 13:05.152
always an alias --

13:05.185 --> 13:06.553
Luther Kelly Jr.

13:06.586 --> 13:09.289
Okay, I'll cross-reference
Sliger's alias

13:09.322 --> 13:11.558
with motels,
flophouses, snitches.

13:11.591 --> 13:13.193
It might take some time,
but if he's using it,

13:13.226 --> 13:14.594
I'll ferret him out.

13:14.627 --> 13:16.463
Fire off a flare
when you do.

13:16.496 --> 13:18.198
We'll be at my place
fixing the roof.

13:18.231 --> 13:19.299
Right, Kyle?
-[ Sighs ]

13:19.332 --> 13:21.034
Sure,
I'll meet you there.

13:21.068 --> 13:22.836
Only I might be
a little late,

13:22.870 --> 13:24.838
so go ahead
and get started without me.
Frank: Really?

13:24.872 --> 13:26.840
Just gonna leave me
with a hole in my house?

13:26.874 --> 13:28.275
And I hope it rains.

13:31.078 --> 13:33.346
He's getting
a little too cocky.
I know.

13:33.380 --> 13:34.514
I like that.

13:36.116 --> 13:37.317
What?

13:37.350 --> 13:38.485
What's wrong with you?

13:38.518 --> 13:40.453
High cholesterol,
anger issues,

13:40.487 --> 13:41.922
excessive drinking,

13:41.955 --> 13:43.857
probably a personality disorder
or two.

13:43.891 --> 13:45.458
Come on, something's up.
Talk to me.

13:45.492 --> 13:47.194
You know what would help?

13:47.227 --> 13:49.362
If you gave me a hand
fixing my roof.
[ Chuckles ]

13:49.396 --> 13:52.032
Hire a contractor,
you cheap ass.

13:57.137 --> 13:59.072
Mrs. Craig:
Mmm, I am good.

13:59.106 --> 14:01.008
This étouffée is
on point.

14:02.409 --> 14:04.411
Hey, come on.

14:04.444 --> 14:06.479
No work
at the supper table.

14:06.513 --> 14:07.981
I know this is your house,

14:08.015 --> 14:10.617
but when I come over to cook,
it's my rules.

14:10.650 --> 14:12.252
Yes, ma'am.

14:14.988 --> 14:16.356
[ Sighs ]

14:16.389 --> 14:18.625
Are these
your father's old files?

14:18.658 --> 14:21.962
Water Street,
Boyle Heights...

14:21.995 --> 14:24.397
Kyle, please, you can't
look into this any further.

14:24.431 --> 14:27.234
Why, Ma?
What do you know?

14:27.267 --> 14:30.003
I know that whatever that is,
it killed your father.

14:30.037 --> 14:32.973
And I see you.
You're acting just like him --

14:33.006 --> 14:35.408
up all night,
looking for breadcrumbs.

14:35.442 --> 14:37.644
And then, by morning,
you're out doing God knows what

14:37.677 --> 14:39.446
with that damn Frank Rourke.
-I know.

14:39.479 --> 14:41.148
I know, you don't like
me working with Frank.

14:41.181 --> 14:42.582
I get it.

14:42.615 --> 14:44.551
Food's on the table.

14:45.618 --> 14:47.220
Thanks, Mom.

14:49.556 --> 14:51.992
Frank's not as bad
as you think.

14:52.025 --> 14:53.326
[ Sighs ]

14:53.360 --> 14:56.596
Your father told me
where Frank comes from...

14:56.629 --> 14:59.132
who he comes from.

14:59.166 --> 15:01.168
He's got evil
in his blood, Kyle.

15:01.201 --> 15:04.037
You don't believe me,
do your research.

15:04.071 --> 15:06.239
Look it up for yourself.

15:08.741 --> 15:11.945
[ Tense music plays ]

15:29.262 --> 15:32.265
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

15:35.002 --> 15:37.037
Hey.

15:37.070 --> 15:39.472
Come to bed, Frank.
It's late.

15:44.211 --> 15:46.046
Ah.

15:46.079 --> 15:47.714
Is this your father?

15:47.747 --> 15:49.349
[ Sighs ]

15:50.350 --> 15:52.319
And look at you.

15:52.352 --> 15:54.621
Wow, what a cutie.

15:54.654 --> 15:56.189
How old?

15:56.223 --> 15:57.624
13.

15:59.792 --> 16:02.629
How come you've never shown me
these before?

16:02.662 --> 16:05.232
Because I don't like
to live in the past.

16:06.433 --> 16:10.103
You know, you never talk
about your dad...

16:10.137 --> 16:11.538
your family.

16:11.571 --> 16:13.406
Why?
Why?

16:13.440 --> 16:14.474
Why?

16:14.507 --> 16:16.676
I'll tell you why.
[ Laughs ]

16:16.709 --> 16:20.247
'Cause there are a lot of nooses
on my family tree.

16:20.280 --> 16:21.648
Rourke men
have a long history

16:21.681 --> 16:26.553
of being crooks,
cheats, liars, thieves.

16:26.586 --> 16:28.621
My daddy was no exception.

16:28.655 --> 16:31.258
That must've been hard
growing up.
[ Chuckles ]

16:31.291 --> 16:33.626
Folks called him a disgrace
on account he brought me up

16:33.660 --> 16:35.695
in the family business.

16:35.728 --> 16:37.264
Only what none
of the good people

16:37.297 --> 16:38.765
of Pecos, Texas,
understood

16:38.798 --> 16:42.669
was that my daddy did it
out of love.

16:42.702 --> 16:44.271
He was raising
his boy to survive

16:44.304 --> 16:46.039
the only way
he knew how.

16:47.340 --> 16:49.509
Emmet: [ Echoing ]
Come on, let's go!

16:49.542 --> 16:52.545
[ Dog barking in distance ]

16:57.817 --> 16:59.252
Hand me my tools.

16:59.286 --> 17:01.454
-You sure about this?
-Of course.

17:01.488 --> 17:03.390
Just some quick cash
to tide us over,

17:03.423 --> 17:05.292
and then we'll pack up,
head to the gulf,
do some fishing.

17:05.325 --> 17:06.526
Don't that sound good?

17:06.559 --> 17:08.428
Let me pull
this robbery with you.

17:08.461 --> 17:10.797
I won't let you down, Daddy.
I can do it.

17:10.830 --> 17:12.299
Oh, I know.

17:12.332 --> 17:14.701
You're the best
crime partner I ever had.

17:14.734 --> 17:16.303
Your time will come.

17:16.336 --> 17:18.738
But as for today,
I need you to stay in the car

17:18.771 --> 17:21.574
while I go and do
what I do best, all right?

17:23.310 --> 17:25.212
One more thing, son --

17:25.245 --> 17:27.347
Once we get there,
don't you blink,

17:27.380 --> 17:29.416
'cause I'll be back in...

17:29.449 --> 17:30.583
Two shakes
of a lamb's tail.
...two shakes
of a lamb's tail.

17:35.188 --> 17:36.523
[ Engine starts ]

17:41.328 --> 17:42.729
[ Horn honks ]

17:44.597 --> 17:46.466
I hate Burbank.

17:46.499 --> 17:48.501
Too many amphetamine-snorting
yipsters

17:48.535 --> 17:50.203
running late
for Bikram yoga.

17:50.237 --> 17:52.705
It's like
a damn demolition derby.

17:52.739 --> 17:54.607
So, what am I doing here?

17:54.641 --> 17:57.210
Tracked Sliger's alias.
He checked in last night.

17:57.244 --> 17:58.645
Considering
this is your case,

17:58.678 --> 18:00.480
thought you might want
to be present for the takedown.

18:00.513 --> 18:01.648
He's in room number 9.

18:01.681 --> 18:05.084
Ladies, shall we?

18:06.419 --> 18:08.621
-Ugh.
-Let's go.

18:08.655 --> 18:11.858
[ Motorhead's
"Shoot You In the Back" plays ]

18:11.891 --> 18:13.826
[ Pounding on door ]

18:14.894 --> 18:18.365
Henry!
No, please.
[ Pistol cocks ]

18:18.398 --> 18:19.499
-Drop the gun!
-Down on the ground!

18:19.532 --> 18:21.234
One in the window!

18:21.268 --> 18:24.371
* They're all fools

18:24.404 --> 18:27.774
* To live by the rules

18:27.807 --> 18:30.343
* The rider wearing black

18:30.377 --> 18:31.778
Henry: Go! Go!

18:31.811 --> 18:33.513
* He's gonna shoot you
in the back, go! *

18:33.546 --> 18:35.915
[ Engine revs ]

18:35.948 --> 18:38.785
**

18:46.259 --> 18:47.360
For the last time, Sliger,

18:47.394 --> 18:49.162
where's Henry
and Bobby Hollister?

18:49.196 --> 18:50.497
Cram it, moon doggy.

18:50.530 --> 18:52.765
Pull the blinds, Tommy.

18:52.799 --> 18:54.667
We'll get him to talk
the old-fashioned way.

18:54.701 --> 18:56.636
[ Grunts ]

18:56.669 --> 18:59.506
Hands off my client, Detective,
or I'll have you up on charges!

18:59.539 --> 19:01.441
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

19:01.474 --> 19:03.243
My bad, Counselor.

19:03.276 --> 19:05.278
I tripped.

19:05.312 --> 19:07.380
-Who are you?
-Your ace in the hole.

19:07.414 --> 19:08.548
Name's Roy Styles,

19:08.581 --> 19:10.317
your court-appointed
public defender.

19:10.350 --> 19:11.784
Don't worry -- I'll have you
out of here in time

19:11.818 --> 19:13.786
for a happy-hour lap dance
at Crazy Girls --

19:13.820 --> 19:15.655
two for one.

19:15.688 --> 19:17.790
I demand a post-haste hearing
to determine the legality

19:17.824 --> 19:21.394
of the search warrant which led
to Mr. Styles' wrongful arrest.

19:21.428 --> 19:22.429
Not so fast.

19:23.430 --> 19:25.432
So we meet again,
Mr. Styles.

19:25.465 --> 19:26.833
Who the hell is he?

19:26.866 --> 19:28.701
Assistant District Attorney
Ronny Cochrane,

19:28.735 --> 19:31.204
cousin of you know who,
may he rest in peace.

19:31.238 --> 19:32.739
He has a perfect
conviction record.

19:32.772 --> 19:34.541
This is bad.
-It is?

19:34.574 --> 19:36.609
The good news is I don't care
about your client, Styles.

19:36.643 --> 19:38.678
I want Bobby
and Henry Hollister.

19:38.711 --> 19:40.680
The bad news
is I'm cutting you loose.

19:40.713 --> 19:43.350
Wait, uh,
why is that bad news?

19:43.383 --> 19:45.485
You're a tethered goat,
Sliger.

19:45.518 --> 19:47.854
We're gonna stake you out there
in plain sight, sit back,

19:47.887 --> 19:49.689
and wait for Henry
to try to kill you again.

19:49.722 --> 19:51.824
Using my client
as -- as bait?

19:51.858 --> 19:53.826
That's outrageous.
My God, you're animals.

19:53.860 --> 19:56.296
He'll never make it out alive.
-Not my problem.

19:56.329 --> 19:58.298
Have a nice day.
-Whoa! Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

19:58.331 --> 20:00.833
Do something, damn it!
-M-Mr. Cochrane.

20:00.867 --> 20:02.302
How about we make a deal?

20:02.335 --> 20:04.604
My client admits his guilt

20:04.637 --> 20:07.574
and gives up everything he knows
about the Hollisters...

20:07.607 --> 20:08.841
I'm listening.

20:08.875 --> 20:10.443
...in exchange
for full immunity.

20:10.477 --> 20:11.744
You hear me, Mr. Cochrane?

20:11.778 --> 20:13.813
We want
a get-out-of-jail-free card.

20:18.818 --> 20:20.453
Fine, Mr. Styles.

20:20.487 --> 20:23.022
[Sighs] Man, you're
the best mouthpiece I ever had.

20:23.055 --> 20:25.992
[ Laughs ]
-Not so fast, Sliger.

20:26.025 --> 20:28.461
First, you got to sing
for your supper.

20:28.495 --> 20:30.463
Tell us where we can find
Henry and Bobby.

20:30.497 --> 20:32.999
[ Sighs ]

20:33.032 --> 20:35.001
I got no idea.
I swear.

20:35.034 --> 20:38.271
But I do know they have
another score lined up,

20:38.305 --> 20:39.939
and it's going down tonight.

20:39.972 --> 20:41.608
-Where?
-Well, we had our little

20:41.641 --> 20:43.810
falling out before he gave up
the details.

20:43.843 --> 20:45.678
All I know
is that Henry said

20:45.712 --> 20:47.780
we had to hit
that jewelry store first,

20:47.814 --> 20:50.750
and only then could we pull
the second score tonight.

20:50.783 --> 20:53.486
Almost, I don't know, like
one was the key to the other.

20:53.520 --> 20:55.488
Hold up -- You're saying
the jewelry store's connected

20:55.522 --> 20:56.523
to the second heist?

21:00.793 --> 21:02.362
Thanks for all your help.

21:02.395 --> 21:04.664
Got to admit,
it was nice working

21:04.697 --> 21:06.433
with law enforcement
for once.

21:06.466 --> 21:07.900
Oh, well, good.

21:07.934 --> 21:10.069
Then you won't mind hanging out
for the next 15 to 20.

21:10.102 --> 21:12.505
Let's go, Sliger.

21:12.539 --> 21:13.806
If we hurry,
you'll make it to county

21:13.840 --> 21:15.708
before they run out
of their famous

21:15.742 --> 21:17.043
cheese-like-substance
sandwiches.
[ Handcuffs click ]

21:17.076 --> 21:18.911
What the hell?
What -- I've got immunity.

21:18.945 --> 21:21.414
Frank: Sorry, homey.
You just got okeydoked.

21:21.448 --> 21:23.416
Didn't he,
Mr. Cochrane?

21:23.450 --> 21:24.917
He sure did,
Mr. Styles.

21:24.951 --> 21:27.387
Don't give us
the hairy eyeball.

21:27.420 --> 21:28.688
We're surprised
you fell for it.

21:34.026 --> 21:35.662
I almost feel bad
for the guy.

21:35.695 --> 21:37.930
-Yeah, right.
-Hey, check this out.

21:37.964 --> 21:39.532
I found a discrepancy

21:39.566 --> 21:41.601
with the merchandise recovered
from the heist.

21:41.634 --> 21:45.805
12 hand-crafted,
diamond-encrusted poker chips.

21:45.838 --> 21:48.007
That jewelry store owner
made no mention of those

21:48.040 --> 21:49.409
on his inventory.

21:49.442 --> 21:52.712
[Scoffs] Got to be worth
2 G's each easy.

21:52.745 --> 21:55.548
No way that guy just forgot
to report losing this much ice.

21:55.582 --> 21:57.450
Son of a bitch.

21:57.484 --> 21:59.919
I just might have an idea
what's going on.

22:04.657 --> 22:06.726
Thanks for coming in,
Mr. Reo.

22:06.759 --> 22:08.361
How you holding up?

22:08.395 --> 22:09.696
Not well.

22:09.729 --> 22:12.965
I can't get Officer Ochoa
out of my head.

22:12.999 --> 22:16.836
His blood's smeared
all into the carpet.

22:16.869 --> 22:19.005
Gus deserved better.

22:19.038 --> 22:21.774
Cheer up.
It's not all bad news.

22:21.808 --> 22:26.646
Look, we got your jewels
and your money back, and...

22:26.679 --> 22:29.348
even your handcrafted
poker chips.

22:30.783 --> 22:32.719
I...

22:32.752 --> 22:34.721
I've never
seen those before.

22:34.754 --> 22:36.523
Sure? Here.

22:36.556 --> 22:38.725
Frank:
Take a closer look.

22:38.758 --> 22:40.359
Look familiar now?
-[ Grunts ]

22:43.496 --> 22:46.599
Do you have any idea
who I am?

22:46.633 --> 22:49.536
The people I know?

22:49.569 --> 22:51.671
You three are done.

22:51.704 --> 22:53.039
I'm gonna have
your jobs.

22:53.072 --> 22:54.841
Mr. Reo.

22:56.909 --> 22:58.878
If these chips
have anything to do

22:58.911 --> 23:01.914
with Officer Ochoa's murder
and you stay silent,

23:01.948 --> 23:03.516
then his blood
is gonna be on more

23:03.550 --> 23:05.151
than just
your nice carpet.

23:05.184 --> 23:07.053
It's gonna be
on your hands.

23:10.923 --> 23:12.859
[ Breathing shakily ]

23:15.595 --> 23:16.563
Let us help you.

23:17.697 --> 23:21.534
Why did you leave these chips
off of your inventory?

23:21.568 --> 23:25.037
They're part of a monthly order
for a special client,

23:25.071 --> 23:28.641
one who pays extra
to keep his name off the books,

23:28.675 --> 23:31.511
the kind who'd skin my hide
for shoes

23:31.544 --> 23:33.780
if he thought
I was even talking to you.

23:33.813 --> 23:35.047
This insignia's familiar,

23:35.081 --> 23:38.050
but I need you
to confirm it for me.

23:38.084 --> 23:40.820
Who did you make these for?

23:40.853 --> 23:42.689
Who's the special client?

23:47.727 --> 23:49.061
Jacques De Leon.

23:49.095 --> 23:51.197
Jacques De Leon,

23:51.230 --> 23:53.533
A.K.A. Jacques the Ripper --

23:53.566 --> 23:55.101
Worst kind of predator.

23:55.134 --> 23:58.471
Skewers victims
for the smallest offenses.

23:58.505 --> 24:00.540
Uses knives, axes --

24:00.573 --> 24:02.742
anything
with a razor-sharp edge.

24:02.775 --> 24:04.677
Runs an underground
poker game.

24:04.711 --> 24:06.946
Different location
every week.

24:06.979 --> 24:10.583
Jacques hands out these chips
to his rich criminal friends

24:10.617 --> 24:12.819
to be used
as single-person entry passes

24:12.852 --> 24:15.154
to these poker matches.

24:15.187 --> 24:17.624
A lot of cash
at those games.

24:17.657 --> 24:19.759
That's got to be
Henry's second heist.

24:19.792 --> 24:21.227
But Henry and Bobby
must've called the heist off.

24:21.260 --> 24:23.763
I mean, they don't have
any of these 12 poker chips.

24:23.796 --> 24:25.231
12 poker chips?

24:25.264 --> 24:27.099
No -- 13.

24:27.133 --> 24:30.169
Jacques always orders
a baker's dozen.

24:33.806 --> 24:36.776
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

24:36.809 --> 24:39.111
So, even if they have
that 13th chip,

24:39.145 --> 24:41.247
it means only one of them can
get into Jacques' poker game.

24:41.280 --> 24:44.851
Tough odds,
even for a cowboy like Henry.

24:44.884 --> 24:48.721
So, will Henry walk away
or take down the score?

24:48.755 --> 24:51.023
Henry and Bobby.

24:51.057 --> 24:53.593
You always talk about
apprehending Henry
but never Bobby,

24:53.626 --> 24:55.528
as if he's some innocent
bystander in all this.

24:55.562 --> 24:57.597
No.
He's just a kid.

24:57.630 --> 25:00.266
[ Somber music plays ]

25:00.299 --> 25:01.601
Like you were?

25:01.634 --> 25:03.302
[ Scoffs ]

25:03.335 --> 25:06.272
I see someone's been Googling
old newspaper articles.

25:06.305 --> 25:07.774
We're not hunting
your father.

25:07.807 --> 25:10.877
You realize that,
right, Frank?

25:10.910 --> 25:13.079
Sorry to disappoint, trainee,
but that comparison's

25:13.112 --> 25:16.883
about as smart
as farting in a space suit.
Fine.

25:16.916 --> 25:18.818
But you once told me
a good cop uses

25:18.851 --> 25:20.620
their own experience
to outwit perps,

25:20.653 --> 25:22.054
so tell me this --

25:22.088 --> 25:24.624
What would your father do
if you were in Henry's shoes,

25:24.657 --> 25:26.025
skip town
and make a run for it

25:26.058 --> 25:28.895
or stay back and risk it all
to rob that poker game?

25:28.928 --> 25:31.297
My daddy? Shoot.

25:31.330 --> 25:35.668
My daddy would never leave cash
on the table.

25:53.352 --> 25:55.187
Woman: I think something's
going on in the pawn shop.

25:55.221 --> 25:57.223
-All right.
-Be careful.

26:27.153 --> 26:31.223
Now, Emmet, we can go ahead
and close each other's eyes,

26:31.257 --> 26:33.860
or you and me
can just talk.

26:36.128 --> 26:38.364
I know that's you
under there.

26:38.397 --> 26:40.299
Come on, Emmet.

26:40.332 --> 26:42.068
Let's talk.

26:44.003 --> 26:45.838
Worst part
of my line of work.

26:45.872 --> 26:48.841
[ Sighs ]
Masks are so damned hot.

26:48.875 --> 26:50.242
This doesn't have
to end badly.

26:50.276 --> 26:52.378
Well, sure it does, Sam.

26:52.411 --> 26:54.714
'Cause I ain't
never going back.
[ Door closes ]

26:54.747 --> 26:55.882
[ Pistol cocks ]
No!

26:58.885 --> 27:00.086
[ Gunshot ]
[ Grunts ]

27:04.791 --> 27:06.659
Daddy?

27:06.693 --> 27:07.927
[ Echoing ] Daddy?

27:07.960 --> 27:10.897
[ Somber music plays ]

27:17.837 --> 27:20.639
[ Rock music plays ]

27:25.177 --> 27:26.212
Now, if I'm right...
[ blows ]

27:26.245 --> 27:28.314
and I'm always right,

27:28.347 --> 27:31.217
Henry and Bobby are
gonna try to take down
Jacques' game tonight.

27:32.451 --> 27:34.754
Well, then, we need
to get there first,

27:34.787 --> 27:36.756
pop those cowboys
when they show up.

27:36.789 --> 27:38.691
So, where's Jacques' game?

27:38.725 --> 27:40.326
How the hell
am I supposed to know?

27:40.359 --> 27:41.961
Aren't you
on a first-name basis

27:41.994 --> 27:43.763
with every lowlife, degenerate
criminal in the country?

27:43.796 --> 27:45.097
Well, yeah.

27:45.131 --> 27:47.033
With Jacques the Ripper,
I'm persona non grata.

27:47.066 --> 27:48.901
Remember the lady who put a hole
in her roof -- now my roof?

27:48.935 --> 27:52.038
Not even a kiss first?

27:52.071 --> 27:53.239
Frank: It just so happens,
at the time,

27:53.272 --> 27:54.941
she was dating
Jacques the Ripper.

27:57.509 --> 27:59.812
Well, that's just great.
Relax, rookie.

27:59.846 --> 28:01.347
There are other ways
to locate the poker game.

28:01.380 --> 28:04.316
Wouldn't Jacques
need to launder the proceeds

28:04.350 --> 28:05.351
from his casino night?

28:06.552 --> 28:09.789
We all know there's only one
person he'd have clean his cash.

28:09.822 --> 28:11.791
Who?

28:11.824 --> 28:12.959
[ Cher's
"Hell on Wheels" plays ]
* Follow you *

28:12.992 --> 28:15.061
* Follow you *

28:15.094 --> 28:16.262
* Follow you *
[ Laughs ]

28:16.295 --> 28:18.130
* Ohh *

28:18.164 --> 28:20.933
* Let's roll

28:20.967 --> 28:24.370
* Hell on wheels, let's roll

28:24.403 --> 28:28.507
* Come on and roll with me

28:28.540 --> 28:30.509
Welcome to
38th Parallel Garments, Inc.,

28:30.542 --> 28:32.078
K-Town's very own DMZ

28:32.111 --> 28:33.813
smack dab in the middle
of the neighborhood.

28:33.846 --> 28:35.481
* Let's rock
See the guy on skates,

28:35.514 --> 28:37.349
looks like he ate
Olivia Newton-John for dinner?

28:37.383 --> 28:39.485
* Let's rock
[ Laughs ]
That's Tiny Tim.

28:39.518 --> 28:43.355
He's a money launderer?
* I want to rock it
with you *

28:43.389 --> 28:45.091
He's sure as hell
no singer.

28:45.124 --> 28:47.760
* I want
to set you free *

28:47.794 --> 28:49.095
* Yeah

28:49.128 --> 28:52.098
* Look ou--
[ Laughs ]

28:52.131 --> 28:54.400
Hey, Frank.
What's up?

28:54.433 --> 28:57.103
Tiny Tim, disco's bad enough
without you weighing in.

28:57.136 --> 28:59.839
Cop, please,
disco is forever,

28:59.872 --> 29:02.541
and Cher is a god.

29:02.574 --> 29:04.143
Now, what do you want?

29:05.144 --> 29:06.745
We need to talk.

29:08.414 --> 29:10.016
Roll with me.

29:13.552 --> 29:17.924
Frank, you're, like, my favorite
morally ambiguous cop,

29:17.957 --> 29:21.127
but no way I'd narc
on Jacques the Ripper.

29:21.160 --> 29:23.529
I understand
you're afraid, Tiny.

29:23.562 --> 29:26.265
The question now is
who are you more afraid of,

29:26.298 --> 29:30.002
Jacques the Ripper
or Roscoe the Executioner.

29:30.036 --> 29:32.171
Who's
Roscoe the Executioner?

29:34.573 --> 29:38.144
[ Laughs ]
What's with all the hostility?

29:38.177 --> 29:39.545
Relax.

29:39.578 --> 29:41.347
Now, where's
the poker game?
[ Pistol cocks ]

29:41.380 --> 29:45.484
* MacArthur's Park
is melting in the dark *

29:45.517 --> 29:47.887
* All the sweet
green ic--

29:47.920 --> 29:49.889
Do you hear
how bad you sound?

29:49.922 --> 29:52.424
Last chance
to boogie, oogie, oogie.

29:52.458 --> 29:54.426
Where's Jacques' game?

29:54.460 --> 29:55.494
I just told you.

29:56.963 --> 29:58.797
MacArthur Park.

30:00.599 --> 30:02.902
You might want to be
more specific.

30:02.935 --> 30:05.304
All I know
is that Jacques said

30:05.337 --> 30:07.073
the game would wrap up
around 3:00

30:07.106 --> 30:09.041
and that it'd
only take them 10 minutes

30:09.075 --> 30:10.342
for them
to bring over the cash

30:10.376 --> 30:14.480
because they were close by
in MacArthur Park.

30:14.513 --> 30:16.082
[ Pistol clicks ]

30:20.119 --> 30:21.353
This is it.

30:23.555 --> 30:26.592
Hey, m-maybe I should
take point on this one.

30:26.625 --> 30:28.094
And why would I do that?

30:28.127 --> 30:29.962
What are you trying to say,
Kyle, huh?

30:29.996 --> 30:32.198
That when it comes
to trigger time, I
won't pull on Henry,

30:32.231 --> 30:33.933
I'll be too busy
humming the chorus

30:33.966 --> 30:35.935
to "Cat's in the Cradle,"
longing for one last game

30:35.968 --> 30:38.204
of catch with Dad
and my aim won't be true?

30:38.237 --> 30:40.506
All I'm saying is that --
Trainee, if you learn
anything riding next to me,

30:40.539 --> 30:42.208
let it be this --

30:42.241 --> 30:43.976
Never question if I'll take down
a target in my sights.

30:44.010 --> 30:45.511
I kill
because it's my nature to.

30:49.181 --> 30:51.183
[ Sighs ]

30:54.686 --> 30:56.388
An ambulance
is on its way, Ranger.

30:56.422 --> 30:57.389
All right.

30:58.290 --> 31:00.092
Ain't no need for that,
now, is there?

31:00.126 --> 31:02.228
[ Breathes shallowly ]

31:02.261 --> 31:04.230
[ Coughs ]

31:04.263 --> 31:07.266
[ Somber music plays ]

31:08.200 --> 31:11.270
You go be
with your daddy now.

31:16.275 --> 31:17.643
[ Voice breaking ]
This is all my fault, Daddy.

31:17.676 --> 31:20.379
No, no.
You did good.

31:20.412 --> 31:23.115
You rushed in
at the first sign of trouble.

31:23.149 --> 31:26.152
That's how
us Rourke men do it.

31:26.185 --> 31:28.454
Look at me, Frank.

31:28.487 --> 31:30.556
This is the part
where I'm supposed to say,

31:30.589 --> 31:33.025
"Son, don't follow
in my footsteps,"

31:33.059 --> 31:35.995
only I just can't do that.

31:36.028 --> 31:39.398
Your great-grandfather,
he robbed trains.

31:39.431 --> 31:41.133
Your granddaddy
took down banks.

31:41.167 --> 31:43.102
And your daddy...

31:44.636 --> 31:46.305
Well, you know
what your daddy did.

31:48.307 --> 31:52.044
And he don't regret
one damn day of it.

31:52.078 --> 31:53.579
But here's the rub --

31:54.580 --> 31:58.017
It always ends like this.

31:58.050 --> 32:00.619
Rourke men never die
of old age.

32:03.522 --> 32:05.424
Quit crying.

32:05.457 --> 32:08.560
Don't shed no tears.
There you go.

32:08.594 --> 32:10.329
Get mean.

32:10.362 --> 32:15.067
If you remember
anything I ever taught you,

32:15.101 --> 32:17.203
remember that.

32:17.236 --> 32:18.604
[ Sighs ]

32:20.239 --> 32:22.574
One more thing --

32:22.608 --> 32:26.178
Don't you blink,
'cause I'll be back in...

32:26.212 --> 32:28.447
Two shakes
of a lamb's tail.
...two shakes...

32:28.480 --> 32:30.082
[ Grunts ]

32:30.116 --> 32:32.718
Kyle: [ Echoing ]
Frank? Frank?

32:32.751 --> 32:35.054
With me there, Frank?

32:35.087 --> 32:36.722
Keep your eyes
on a swivel.

32:36.755 --> 32:39.358
They're out here.
I can feel it.

32:42.361 --> 32:45.364
[ Dramatic music plays ]

32:48.100 --> 32:50.502
[ Doorbell buzzes ]

32:50.536 --> 32:51.503
Yeah?

32:52.504 --> 32:53.905
What do you want?

32:57.776 --> 32:59.378
Follow me.

33:05.317 --> 33:06.652
Sir, I need to inspect
your buy-in.

33:10.122 --> 33:13.125
[ Metal detector warbling ]

33:15.127 --> 33:18.097
[ Metal detector squeaks ]

33:18.130 --> 33:20.099
What do you got
in your pants?

33:20.132 --> 33:21.267
You hitting on me,
mister?

33:22.601 --> 33:25.537
Kidding.
Here, let me show you.

33:25.571 --> 33:27.139
Hell's all this?

33:31.343 --> 33:33.312
[ People screaming ]

33:36.715 --> 33:41.320
Ladies and gentlemen,
it is time to stand and deliver!

33:41.353 --> 33:45.391
Your money or your life?

33:45.424 --> 33:47.426
That's it.

33:47.459 --> 33:48.794
[ People scream ]

33:48.827 --> 33:52.531
Who else wants to go all in?
You?

33:52.564 --> 33:54.500
Fill her up, hoss.

34:03.342 --> 34:06.312
Don't have to be neat, buddy.
Throw it in there.

34:06.345 --> 34:08.447
Double time.
[ Zipper clicks ]

34:10.849 --> 34:12.050
Gracias.

34:15.621 --> 34:17.289
Well, you must be Jacques.

34:17.323 --> 34:20.192
And you must be a dead man
hitting my spot like this.

34:20.226 --> 34:22.060
Wait, what's that
on your nose?

34:22.794 --> 34:26.165
[Grunts] Aah!
Blood.
[ People shout ]

34:26.198 --> 34:28.567
Have a nice evening, folks.

34:28.600 --> 34:32.070
[ Explosion, people scream ]

34:40.212 --> 34:42.314
That's Bobby.
Here we go.

34:42.348 --> 34:45.351
[ Dramatic music continues ]

34:48.387 --> 34:49.755
[ Door closes ]

34:58.630 --> 35:00.866
-Hey.
-Nice work, Pop.

35:00.899 --> 35:03.135
Here you go, buddy.
I'm gonna secure the door.
All right.

35:05.571 --> 35:07.473
[ Glass shatters ]

35:07.506 --> 35:09.107
Bobby?

35:10.509 --> 35:11.877
Bobby, look out!

35:11.910 --> 35:13.879
[ Grunts ]
Aah!

35:13.912 --> 35:15.881
Evening, Henry.
[ Pistols cock ]

35:15.914 --> 35:17.549
Well...

35:17.583 --> 35:20.886
I guess this is what they call
a Mexican standoff.

35:20.919 --> 35:23.422
Now, the way I see it,

35:23.455 --> 35:25.624
we can go ahead
and close each other's eyes,

35:25.657 --> 35:27.193
or...

35:29.661 --> 35:31.363
you and me can just talk.

35:31.397 --> 35:33.232
Frank,
what are you doing?

35:33.265 --> 35:35.367
How about it, Henry?

35:35.401 --> 35:37.135
Let's talk.

35:41.407 --> 35:42.674
Henry, you don't have
to die here.

35:42.708 --> 35:45.277
Considering
your pistol's at your side,

35:45.311 --> 35:47.879
I reckon you'll be the one
in the bone orchard come Sunday.

35:47.913 --> 35:50.782
Sure, you can kill me,
but, see, the guy at my 6:00?

35:50.816 --> 35:53.485
You got him?
In my sights
ready to execute.

35:53.519 --> 35:55.687
That's Kyle Craig,
former U.S. Marine.

35:55.721 --> 35:58.357
Could shoot a pimento
out of an olive at 25 yards.

35:58.390 --> 36:00.226
He'll have no trouble
making your funeral

36:00.259 --> 36:01.760
a closed-casket service.

36:01.793 --> 36:03.829
But you'll be dead
right along with me, lawman.

36:03.862 --> 36:05.497
I'm fine with that --

36:05.531 --> 36:07.799
blaze of glory,
killed in the line --

36:07.833 --> 36:09.968
only what about your son?

36:10.001 --> 36:11.937
He'll be convicted
of those robberies,

36:11.970 --> 36:14.840
plus do time for the killing
of that jewelry-store guard

36:14.873 --> 36:16.375
and the slaying of a cop.

36:16.408 --> 36:20.246
That is,
if you pull that trigger.
So what?

36:20.279 --> 36:23.415
You gonna offer me
a reduced sentence?

36:23.449 --> 36:25.317
I know
you can't make deals.

36:25.351 --> 36:26.818
You don't have
the power.

36:26.852 --> 36:30.656
No, but I have my word,
and I'm giving it to you.

36:30.689 --> 36:32.391
Surrender now.

36:32.424 --> 36:35.394
I'll cash in some IOUs
at the D.A.'s office.

36:35.427 --> 36:36.662
You'll get
life without parole.

36:36.695 --> 36:38.797
Bobby will be out in 10.
Don't do it, Pop.

36:38.830 --> 36:40.466
Henry, that's
your only son behind me,

36:40.499 --> 36:42.668
your final mark
on this world.

36:42.701 --> 36:45.471
And right here, right now,
you've got one last chance

36:45.504 --> 36:47.539
to give him
something to build on.

36:47.573 --> 36:50.709
Please,
give Bobby a better life.

36:50.742 --> 36:53.745
[ Dramatic music plays ]

36:57.349 --> 37:00.452
You look me
in the eye, lawman.

37:00.486 --> 37:02.588
Are you
a man of your word?

37:02.621 --> 37:05.324
It's the only good thing
I got left.

37:31.082 --> 37:32.451
[ Grunts ]

37:32.484 --> 37:34.586
Pop! Pop!

37:34.620 --> 37:35.754
Hey, Rourke!

37:38.524 --> 37:39.491
[ Knife clatters ]

37:39.525 --> 37:40.926
Pop!

37:42.394 --> 37:44.396
Henry: [ Grunting ]

37:48.934 --> 37:52.704
Don't worry.
I'll keep my word.

37:55.574 --> 37:58.410
Kyle, let the kid come
to his father.

37:58.444 --> 38:00.412
[ Gasping ]

38:01.513 --> 38:03.382
[ Voice breaking ]
Pop. Pop.

38:03.415 --> 38:06.485
-Bobby.
-Come on, g-get up.

38:06.518 --> 38:09.521
[ Somber music plays ]

38:11.823 --> 38:13.825
[ Sobs ]

38:19.931 --> 38:22.868
[ Police radio chatter ]

38:23.969 --> 38:25.303
Uh, give us a moment.

38:28.707 --> 38:30.709
Glad you're
still here, Ranger.

38:30.742 --> 38:32.678
-Is that a fact?
-Yep.

38:32.711 --> 38:34.713
'Cause I want you
to know something.

38:34.746 --> 38:36.515
You're a dead man.

38:36.548 --> 38:37.983
Not today,

38:38.016 --> 38:40.852
but sooner or later,
I'm gonna kill you.

38:42.754 --> 38:44.656
No, you're not.

38:44.690 --> 38:47.125
Let me tell you
what you are gonna do.

38:47.158 --> 38:48.994
You're gonna do
exactly as I say,

38:49.027 --> 38:51.597
so pay real close attention,
kid.

38:51.630 --> 38:54.600
[ Echoing ] 'Cause I'm only
gonna speak this once.

38:59.104 --> 39:00.839
So, what's all this about --

39:00.872 --> 39:03.842
you hooking up Jesse James Jr.
with a reduced sentence?

39:03.875 --> 39:06.478
This is my case, Frank.
That's my call.

39:06.512 --> 39:08.847
You know I got juice at
the D.A.'s office, too, right?

39:08.880 --> 39:10.816
And I'll wager a bottle
of whatever moonshine

39:10.849 --> 39:12.751
you put yourself
to sleep with every night

39:12.784 --> 39:14.986
that my contact
outranks yours.

39:15.020 --> 39:16.855
Well, first off,
moonshine comes in jugs,

39:16.888 --> 39:18.990
not bottles,
and second, go ahead.

39:19.024 --> 39:21.727
Be a complete prick
and trump my play...

39:21.760 --> 39:23.462
-[ Scoffs ]
-...or shake my hand and say,

39:23.495 --> 39:25.030
"Frank, thanks for calling up
on my case."

39:25.063 --> 39:26.632
Choice is yours.

39:29.501 --> 39:32.504
-[ Chuckles ]
-Next time, check with me first.

39:35.507 --> 39:36.908
I hope he's worth it.

39:42.681 --> 39:44.650
Hey, guys,
give me a sec, will you?

39:48.920 --> 39:51.122
What do you want?

39:51.156 --> 39:54.493
For you to do exactly
what I say,

39:54.526 --> 39:55.927
so pay
close attention, kid,

39:55.961 --> 39:58.163
'cause I'm
only speaking this once.

39:58.196 --> 40:00.999
You're about to be sent
into a den of hyenas,

40:01.032 --> 40:02.501
where most men come out
feral beasts

40:02.534 --> 40:05.904
stripped of their humanity,
but not you.

40:05.937 --> 40:08.640
Do your time with your head down
and your mouth shut.

40:08.674 --> 40:12.143
Don't join a gang.
Don't hustle on the side.

40:12.177 --> 40:15.080
Swear to that,
and I'll shepherd you through.

40:16.915 --> 40:19.518
Why would you do that
for me?

40:19.551 --> 40:22.020
'Cause we're both
our father's sons.

40:22.053 --> 40:24.656
But that doesn't
have to define us --

40:24.690 --> 40:27.092
not you and not me.

40:33.231 --> 40:34.700
Good luck, Bobby.

40:47.946 --> 40:50.516
Sun's gonna be up soon.

40:50.549 --> 40:52.050
We should probably head
over to your house then.

40:52.083 --> 40:54.119
Why?

40:56.087 --> 40:58.690
[ Mid-tempo music plays,
hammer pounding ]

40:58.724 --> 41:00.125
[ Grunts ]

41:02.628 --> 41:04.696
[ Both sigh ]

41:04.730 --> 41:07.966
Well, you don't suck,
trainee.

41:07.999 --> 41:09.535
I help you fix your house,

41:09.568 --> 41:11.703
and that's the nicest thing
you can say?

41:11.737 --> 41:14.239
I'm not talking
about your roofing skills.

41:14.272 --> 41:16.942
Truth is, as a carpenter,
you're crap.
[ Chuckles ]

41:16.975 --> 41:20.145
But being a cop,
you don't suck.

41:22.848 --> 41:24.482
I've been meaning
to ask you a question.

41:25.116 --> 41:27.586
I uncovered your old
foster-care records.

41:27.619 --> 41:29.721
Said your foster father
was Sam O'Keefe,

41:29.755 --> 41:32.691
the Texas Ranger who took you
and your father down.

41:32.724 --> 41:33.959
Waiting
for a question, Kyle.

41:33.992 --> 41:35.827
Seems like
you got all the answers.

41:35.861 --> 41:37.996
What was that like,

41:38.029 --> 41:40.766
being raised by the cop
who killed your old man?

41:57.649 --> 41:59.150
That was a long time ago.

41:59.184 --> 42:01.286
It's all a blur now.

42:01.319 --> 42:03.555
Sam still around?

42:04.623 --> 42:06.992
Nope.
Killed in the line of duty.

42:07.025 --> 42:08.960
Sorry.

42:11.296 --> 42:13.031
Go out
in a blaze of glory?

42:13.064 --> 42:15.767
Damn straight he did.

42:15.801 --> 42:17.669
Just like your old man.

42:19.037 --> 42:21.640
To Ranger Sam O'Keefe.

42:21.673 --> 42:23.341
To Detective Billy Craig.

42:23.374 --> 42:24.943
[ Bottles clink ]

42:31.082 --> 42:33.084
[ Siren wails in distance ]

42:42.728 --> 42:46.732
**
